97 fairly reflects the effects of inflation and deflation on residents of this state.
98 (g) The exemption granted by subsection (b) of this section shall apply to all taxable years
99 beginning on or after January 1, 2026.
100 SECTION 2.
101 In accordance with the requirements of Article VII, Section II of the Constitution of the State
102 of Georgia, this Act shall not become law unless it receives the requisite two-thirds' majority
103 vote in both the Senate and the House of Representatives.
104 SECTION 3.
105 The municipal election superintendent of the City of Walnut Grove shall call and conduct an
106 election as provided in this section for the purpose of submitting this Act to the electors of
107 the City of Walnut Grove for approval or rejection. The election superintendent shall
108 conduct that election on the Tuesday following the first Monday in November of 2025 and
109 shall issue the call and conduct that election as provided by general law. The election
110 superintendent shall cause the date and purpose of the election to be published once a week
111 for two weeks immediately preceding the date thereof in the official organ of Walton County.
112 The ballot shall have written or printed thereon the words:
113 "( ) YES Shall the Act be approved which provides a homestead exemption from City
114 of Walnut Grove ad valorem taxes for municipal purposes in an amount
115 ( ) NO equal to the amount by which the current year assessed value of a
116 homestead exceeds the adjusted base year assessed value, including any
117 final determination of value on appeal pursuant to Code Section 48-5-311
118 of the O.C.G.A., as amended, of such homestead?"
119 All persons desiring to vote for approval of the Act shall vote "Yes," and all persons desiring
120 to vote for rejection of the Act shall vote "No." If more than one-half of the votes cast on
